Landscape is a continuous code quality inspector for Python projects.

By enabling this hook, Landscape will listen for pushes and on each push, instigate a new code check.

Install Notes
-------------

Landscape will automatically install this hook, there is no need to do it manually.

To install:

1.  Create an account at https://landscape.io (you can sign in with GitHub)
2.  Enable checking on a repository. The hook will be automatically installed.

For more information about Landscape, see https://landscape.io/docs/